{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba954cce-a92e-4eb7-a879-bd1de27759a1","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since this is a general guidance request rather than an existing codebase, here's exactly what to do:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `xmlns` for your ViewModel namespace and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Emit warnings for broken bindings during compilation -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler resolves bindings against `SettingsViewModel` **at compile time**. If you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n### Key rules\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|---|---|\n| Set `x:DataType` on root or any container element | Leave it off — bindings stay interpreted at runtime |\n| Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` to opt out in a subtree (e.g., for `CommandParameter` with different type) | Mix compiled and non-compiled bindings without explicitly opting out |\n| Keep `Binding` paths matching exact property names & types | Use string-only paths that don't exist on the declared type |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c996b895-38be-476f-8671-11db35df43a9","outputTokens":655,"requestId":"B80B:18AE3E:123394:17EE11:69FFD779"},"id":"9ced3873-a250-47c8-b58f-c865aa55e980","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:55:33.492Z","parentId":"6de87743-ef31-4f75-bcf3-ab866c2ef9d5"}
